idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows 2000 Version 5.0 (Build 2195) Service Pack 3; ESRI ArcCatalog 8.3.0.800

descript.abstract: World Countries 1992 represents the boundaries for the countries of the world, as they existed in 1992 showing the Soviet Union, Yugoslavia, and Czechoslovakia as single nations.
descript.purpose: World Countries 1992 provides political boundaries for the world in 1992. To display World Political Organization Membership attributes or CountryWatch Demographics attributes, join these tables to this attribute table using Fips_cntry or Cntry_name as the common field.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data: 1:15,000,000.

distinfo.techpreq: To use this data requires software that supports SDC files.

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted the features from ESRI Data & Maps 1999 data set-cntry98.shp. Edited the countries to reflect which existed in 1992 based on ESRI Data & Maps 1999 data set-cntry92.shp. Extended political boundaries into the Caspian Sea and removed the shoreline. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr). Created ArcView GIS legend file (.avl). Created projection file (.prj). Created spatial indices.

citeinfo.origin: United States Department of State, Bureau of Intelligence and Research
citeinfo.title: Geographic and Global Issues Quarterly

pubinfo.publish: United States Department of State, Bureau of Intelligence and Research

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: Added attribute COLOR_MAP from World Countries 2002. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices. Converted the data set to SDC.

horizpa.horizpar: The geospatial part of this data set was originally extracted from the ArcWorld Supplement database and then generalized (tolerance unknown). The positional accuracy is unknown.

dataqual.logic: No duplicate features are present. The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format in ArcSDE®. This verifies and validates the geometry. The data set is created directly from a topologically correct ArcInfo™ coverage.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
